{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:john.7",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "john",
    "chapterNumber": 7,
    "referenceLabel": "John 7",
    "summary": "Source text for John 7 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:1",
      "text": "After these things Jesus walked in Galilee: for he would not walk in Jewry, because the Jews sought to kill him.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:2",
      "text": "Now the Jews’ feast of tabernacles was at hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:3",
      "text": "His brethren therefore said unto him, Depart hence, and go into Judea, that thy disciples also may see the works that thou doest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:4",
      "text": "For there is no man that doeth any thing in secret, and he himself seeketh to be known openly. If thou do these things, shew thyself to the world.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:5",
      "text": "For neither did his brethren believe in him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:6",
      "text": "Then Jesus said unto them, My time is not yet come: but your time is alway ready.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:7",
      "text": "The world cannot hate you; but me it hateth, because I testify of it, that the works thereof are evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:8",
      "text": "Go ye up unto this feast: I go not up yet unto this feast; for my time is not yet full come.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:9",
      "text": "When he had said these words unto them, he abode still in Galilee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:10",
      "text": "But when his brethren were gone up, then went he also up unto the feast, not openly, but as it were in secret.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:11",
      "text": "Then the Jews sought him at the feast, and said, Where is he?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:12",
      "text": "And there was much murmuring among the people concerning him: for some said, He is a good man: others said, Nay; but he deceiveth the people.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:13",
      "text": "Howbeit no man spake openly of him for fear of the Jews.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:14",
      "text": "Now about the midst of the feast Jesus went up into the temple, and taught.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:15",
      "text": "And the Jews marvelled, saying, How knoweth this man letters, having never learned?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:16",
      "text": "Jesus answered them, and said, My doctrine is not mine, but his that sent me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:17",
      "text": "If any man will do his will, he shall know of the doctrine, whether it be of God, or whether I speak of myself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:18",
      "text": "He that speaketh of himself seeketh his own glory: but he that seeketh his glory that sent him, the same is true, and no unrighteousness is in him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:19",
      "text": "Did not Moses give you the law, and yet none of you keepeth the law? Why go ye about to kill me?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:20",
      "text": "The people answered and said, Thou hast a devil: who goeth about to kill thee?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:21",
      "text": "Jesus answered and said unto them, I have done one work, and ye all marvel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:22",
      "text": "Moses therefore gave unto you circumcision; (not because it is of Moses, but of the fathers;) and ye on the sabbath day circumcise a man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:23",
      "text": "If a man on the sabbath day receive circumcision, that the law of Moses should not be broken; are ye angry at me, because I have made a man every whit whole on the sabbath day?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:24",
      "text": "Judge not according to the appearance, but judge righteous judgment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:25",
      "text": "Then said some of them of Jerusalem, Is not this he, whom they seek to kill?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:26",
      "text": "But, lo, he speaketh boldly, and they say nothing unto him. Do the rulers know indeed that this is the very Christ?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:27",
      "text": "Howbeit we know this man whence he is: but when Christ cometh, no man knoweth whence he is.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:28",
      "text": "Then cried Jesus in the temple as he taught, saying, Ye both know me, and ye know whence I am: and I am not come of myself, but he that sent me is true, whom ye know not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:29",
      "text": "But I know him: for I am from him, and he hath sent me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:30",
      "text": "Then they sought to take him: but no man laid hands on him, because his hour was not yet come.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.31",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:31",
      "text": "And many of the people believed on him, and said, When Christ cometh, will he do more miracles than these which this man hath done?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.32",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:32",
      "text": "The Pharisees heard that the people murmured such things concerning him; and the Pharisees and the chief priests sent officers to take him.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.33",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:33",
      "text": "Then said Jesus unto them, Yet a little while am I with you, and then I go unto him that sent me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.34",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:34",
      "text": "Ye shall seek me, and shall not find me: and where I am, thither ye cannot come.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.35",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:35",
      "text": "Then said the Jews among themselves, Whither will he go, that we shall not find him? will he go unto the dispersed among the Gentiles, and teach the Gentiles?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.36",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:36",
      "text": "What manner of saying is this that he said, Ye shall seek me, and shall not find me: and where I am, thither ye cannot come?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.37",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:37",
      "text": "In the last day, that great day of the feast, Jesus stood and cried, saying, If any man thirst, let him come unto me, and drink.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.38",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:38",
      "text": "He that believeth on me, as the scripture hath said, out of his belly shall flow rivers of living water.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.39",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:39",
      "text": "(But this spake he of the Spirit, which they that believe on him should receive: for the Holy Ghost was not yet given; because that Jesus was not yet glorified.)",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.40",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:40",
      "text": "Many of the people therefore, when they heard this saying, said, Of a truth this is the Prophet.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.41",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:41",
      "text": "Others said, This is the Christ. But some said, Shall Christ come out of Galilee?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.42",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:42",
      "text": "Hath not the scripture said, That Christ cometh of the seed of David, and out of the town of Bethlehem, where David was?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.43",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:43",
      "text": "So there was a division among the people because of him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.44",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:44",
      "text": "And some of them would have taken him; but no man laid hands on him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.45",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:45",
      "text": "Then came the officers to the chief priests and Pharisees; and they said unto them, Why have ye not brought him?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.46",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:46",
      "text": "The officers answered, Never man spake like this man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.47",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:47",
      "text": "Then answered them the Pharisees, Are ye also deceived?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.48",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:48",
      "text": "Have any of the rulers or of the Pharisees believed on him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.49",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 49,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:49",
      "text": "But this people who knoweth not the law are cursed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.50",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 50,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:50",
      "text": "Nicodemus saith unto them, (he that came to Jesus by night, being one of them,)",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.51",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 51,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:51",
      "text": "Doth our law judge any man, before it hear him, and know what he doeth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.52",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 52,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:52",
      "text": "They answered and said unto him, Art thou also of Galilee? Search, and look: for out of Galilee ariseth no prophet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:john.7.53",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 53,
      "referenceLabel": "John 7:53",
      "text": "And every man went unto his own house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
